.
.
It's September and my little boy turns two soon. I have always decided to breastfeed till he turns two. 
.
.
I must say though, I am feeling so anxious about the idea of stopping such a comforting practice. A practice of bonding, connection, love and much more! 
.
.
I am however determined that in two weeks I need to stop. However I do have an issue with the idea of stopping "cold turkey" .. I do not know if that is OK emotionally.
.
.
So I have started implementing the following to ease the process 
.
.
.
‚ú®Be very honest with your little one and tell them that breastfeeding will end soon. Each day you breastfeed remind them of it nicely and gently.
.
.
‚ú® While doing that ensure that your child is sitting on your lap and you are connecting with him/her through your eyes  and showing them so much affection. 
.
.
‚ú®Remember they need to know that this is not a rejection but it's part of growing up and becoming more independent.
.
.
‚ú®Start introducing other soothing practises in place that will replace breastfeeding such as a soft toy, colourful pillow, new milk bottle, new bed linen that gives them excitement and attraction to go to bed, or just a t-shirt that smells like mom. 
.
.
